{
  "stem": "1918.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 318.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one kid or another was always on top of the kitchen table reciting the latest poem that appeared in one of the magazines or newspapers.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was a very-- poetry was a very important thing in my day, in my country.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were smitten by it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And somebody was always reciting poetry or imitating an actress from a movie.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was a very colorful household.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And all of the friends that each of us had would flock to my home because it was such a special home.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In the same religious household such as ours, the lifestyle was very different.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there were even more children in those homes than in ours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had six, but they had sometimes 10, 12, or 14 children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they were literally driven out of their homes, and they ran to ours to listen to poetry and talk about books.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And, you know, it probably sounds kind of strange to talk in such a positive cultural way about a little town like Kisvarda.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But my god, that's how it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It really was in my home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, she was-- you know, somebody-- the main meal took place lunchtime.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if somebody walked in at lunchtime, my mother would just say, I'll just put more water in the soup.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the person automatically would be invited to stay for dinner.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a lot of cleaning for the Shabbat and a lot of baking of the challah.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and all those-- what is it called that we eat on Saturday morning?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The danishes, you know?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Prune danish and-- you don't have it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But prune danish and cheese danish and all kinds of-- lots of stuff for six growing kids.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Lots of stuff to be baked.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
